Pomegranate Cheesecake

This luscious pomegranate cheesecake combines creamy layers with a vibrant fruit glaze and crunchy seeds. Its perfect for holidays, special gatherings, or any time you crave a beautiful and delicious dessert.

Ingredients

  • 200g graham crackers or digestive biscuits, crushed
  • 75g melted butter
  • 500g cream cheese (softened)
  • 150g sugar
  • 2 eggs
  • 200ml sour cream
  • 1 tsp vanilla extract
  • 1 cup pomegranate juice
  • 2 tbsp cornstarch
  • Pomegranate seeds for topping

Cooking Instructions

  1. Preheat your oven to 160C (320F). Line or grease a springform pan.
  2. Mix crushed crackers and melted butter. Press firmly into the base of the pan. Bake for 10 minutes and let cool.
  3. Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Add eggs one at a time, then mix in sour cream and vanilla.
  4. Pour over the crust and bake for 5060 minutes until set but slightly jiggly in the center.
  5. Cool at room temperature, then refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight.
  6. For the glaze: simmer pomegranate juice and cornstarch until thick. Let cool, then pour over the chilled cheesecake.
  7. Top with fresh pomegranate seeds before serving.

Tips & Calories

  • Use full-fat cream cheese for the best texture.
  • You can make the crust with nuts or oats for variety.
  • Dont overmix the batter to avoid cracking.
  • Approximate Calories: 340 kcal per slice (1/12 of cake)
